			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">How bard focus should be done.<a name="62354"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 16 04 8:32 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><i>Repost from SOE class boards, where I posted it originally.</i>
<br />
 
<br />
Our focus songs should not decrease in effectiveness as they are used on higher lvl spells.  The spell focus should be 30%, 35% so that we are not decreasing in value, or even flatlining as we progress.
<br />
 
<br />
Ideally, bard focus songs should be a modifier added after all other focus effects are applied.
<br />
 
<br />
Take 3 points lvl 60, 65, and 70;  Assume average of 10%, 20%, and 30% focus worn by casters worn at each respective level.
<br />
 
<br />
Right now our worst focus is 15% shortly after 60.  Average worn focus of 10%.  125/110= 13.6% actual focus.
<br />
Next best is 25% focus at 65. Average worn focus is 20%. 145/120 = 20.8% actual focus.
<br />
Best focus is 30% at 70.  Average worn focus is 30%.  160/130 = 23.5% actual focus.
<br />
 
<br />
So make our focus apply after all other focus effects so that our song line-up looks like such.  Remember this isn't focus that stack, this is focus applied after all other focus effects.
<br />
 
<br />
-63 Forpor's - 15% focus DD only
<br />
-64 Rizlo's    - 15% focus all detrimental, +10% spell haste.
<br />
-65 Muse      - 20% focus all detrimental
<br />
-65 Echo      - 20% focus all detrimental, +10% spell haste.
<br />
 
<br />
Two different paths to go with the OoW songs:
<br />
 
<br />
-68 Yelhun   - 25% focus DD only
<br />
-69 Eriki       - 25% focus all detrimental
<br />
-70 Ancient  - 25% focus all detrimental + 10% spell haste.
<br />
 
<br />
OR (this is the line I prefer)
<br />
 
<br />
-68 Yelhun   - 25% focus DD only
<br />
-69 Eriki       - 25% focus all detrimental + 10% spell haste
<br />
-70 Ancient  - 30% focus all detrimental
<br />
 
<br />
Make the overhaste component scale accordingly:
<br />
 
<br />
-15%/15%
<br />
-20%/20%
<br />
-25%/25%
<br />
-30%/30%
<br />
 
<br />
=========================================================
<br />
 
<br />
By reconfiguring the way focus is applied, and adjusting bards songs to scale appropriately as they level, bards do not have the problem they have now of decreasing in value as they (and their guild) progress further into the game.
<br />
 
<br />
=========================================================
<br />
 
<br />
The following is in my opinion the absolute pinnacle of how these songs should be set up.
<br />
 
<br />
-63 Forpor's - 15% focus DD only,            10% mana preservation,   15% overhaste
<br />
-64 Rizlo's    - 15% focus all detrimental,  10% spell haste,                15% overhaste
<br />
-65 Muse      - 20% focus all detrimental,                                             20% overhaste
<br />
-65 Echo      - 20% focus all detrimental,  10% spell haste,                 20% overhaste
<br />
-68 Yelhun   - 25% focus DD only,            10% mana preservation,    25% overhaste
<br />
-69 Eriki       - 25% focus all detrimental,   10% spell haste,                25% overhaste
<br />
-70 Ancient  - 30% focus all detrimental,                                              30% overhaste
<br />
 
<br />
This is a bardic line of songs.  Each song brings it's own unique advantage/disadvantage to the table, and makes a bard have to stop and think &quot;hmmmmm, who is in my group, and what song should I sing accordingly?&quot;.  That was part of what the fun of playing a bard used to be... learning what songs to select for different situations, and NEVER having enough slots to keep them all memmed so you had to pick and choose what would work best.
<br />
 
<br />
I didn't think I could add anything more to this perfect plan, but then it just hit me.  Instead of the lvl 70 song being a rare drop:
<br />
 
<br />
Why not have the lvl 70 focus songs be three songs that are quested in an epic fashion, and gained sequentially like the rest of our songs.
<br />
 
<br />
First part of song epic
<br />
-70 Ancient1  - 30% focus DD only,                                                                     25% overhaste
<br />
 
<br />
Second part of song epic
<br />
-70 Ancient2  - 30% all detrimental,                                                                     30% overhaste
<br />
 
<br />
Third part of song epic
<br />
-70 Ancient3  - 35% all detrimental,      10% spell haste/mana preservation,     35% overhaste
<br />
 
<br />
First part you can do solo, Second part with a couple of appropriately progressed groups, and Third with a full on raid encounter.
<br />
Every musician aspires to have their one grand overture, their one greatest work. 
<br />
 
<br />
Forpar had his symphony, why can't EQ bards aspire to have their own epic masterpiece.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
